#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""charmm-test -- unified CLI for CHARMM Slurm build/test/grade pipeline.

A single tool replacing the dozen scripts that previously made up the
CHARMM testing pipeline. It manages the full lifecycle: submitting Slurm
build and test jobs, grading results with numerical tolerance, promoting
outputs to benchmarks, and archiving old results.

Subcommands:
    list        Show all build/test configurations
    build       Submit Slurm build jobs (pulls latest CHARMM source first)
    test        Submit Slurm test jobs
    run         Build then test, chained via Slurm dependencies
    grade       Grade test results with numerical tolerance comparison
    status      Show active Slurm jobs
    bench       Promote test output to benchmark
    clean       Archive old test results
    prereqs     Check that all prerequisites are in place

Example usage::

    charmm-test list
    charmm-test run gpu sccdftb
    charmm-test status
    charmm-test grade --tol 0.001

Prerequisites:
    See ``charmm-test prereqs`` or the `Prerequisites` section below.

Generating documentation:
    This script is self-documenting via docstrings. Generate HTML docs with::

        pdoc ./charmm-test -o docs/

    Or, if pdoc requires a ``.py`` extension::

        ln -s charmm-test charmm_test.py && pdoc charmm_test -o docs/

Prerequisites
-------------
This script expects a specific directory layout under ``~/testing/``
(configurable via `TESTING_HOME`):

Directory layout::

    ~/testing/
    ├── charmm-test          # this script
    ├── setup.bash           # one-time environment setup
    ├── charmm/              # CHARMM source (git clone)
    │   ├── tool/
    │   │   └── NewCharmmTree
    │   ├── configure
    │   └── ...
    ├── env/
    │   └── test/            # conda/micromamba environment prefix
    ├── sccdftb_data/        # (optional) SCCDFTB parameters
    │   └── sccdftb.dat
    └── install-<name>/      # per-config build trees (created by build)
        ├── configure
        ├── build/cmake/
        └── test/
            ├── test.com
            ├── bench/       # benchmark outputs
            ├── output/      # test outputs
            └── output.rpt   # diff report from test.com

Required software (available in the conda env or via modules):

- **Python 3.8+** (stdlib only -- no third-party packages needed)
- **Slurm** (sbatch, squeue) on the cluster
- **Ninja** build system
- **CMake** (called by CHARMM's ``./configure``)
- **Fortran/C/C++ compilers** (gcc, gfortran, or Intel via modules)
- **MPI** (OpenMPI or Intel MPI) for parallel test configs
- **CUDA toolkit** for GPU configs (gpu, gpu2)
- **tcsh** (``/usr/bin/tcsh``) for running ``test.com``
- **Git** for pulling latest CHARMM source

The conda environment at ``env/test/`` should provide compilers, cmake,
ninja, fftw, openmm, and any other libraries needed by ``./configure``.
See ``setup.bash`` for the exact ``conda create`` invocation.

Cluster environment modules (loaded by embedded Slurm scripts):

- ``anaconda/miniconda-latest`` -- provides ``conda`` command
- The conda env at ``~/testing/env/test`` must be pre-created

Note: This script itself runs on the **login node** (submitting jobs).
The actual builds and tests run inside Slurm jobs on compute nodes.
"""

